title: What to know about the sexual assault video and violence in India’s Manipur
description: A video showing two women being sexually assaulted sparked outrage in India. Here's what to know about the clip and the wider violence in Manipur state.

title: U.S. in no hurry to provide Ukraine with long-range missiles
description: The Biden administration is refusing to send long-range missiles to Ukraine despite mounting pressure from U.S. lawmakers and pleas from the government in Kyiv.

title: Google, Meta fight with Canada over law forcing them to pay for news
description: Canada’s battle echoes frustrations in places around the world about power imbalances resulting from the tech giants’ dominance.

title: Ukraine is now the most mined country. It will take decades to make safe
description: In a year and a half of conflict, Ukraine has become the world’s most mined country. Unexploded ordnance has contaminated an area larger than Florida.

title: Ukraine live briefing: World on brink of food crisis due to Russian action, Zelensky says
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky told Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdogan that allowing grain exports through the Black Sea is an “absolute priority.”

title: What Russia’s exit from grain deal means for wheat prices
description: Russia’s announcement that it would renew its naval blockade on Ukrainian ports has revived concerns about wheat prices.
